<TITLE> Alleged outlaw arrested in Narail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Narail, July 2 (bdnews24.com)Police arrested alleged regional leader Maruf Hossain of the outlawed Biplobi Communist Party in Narail on Wednesday night. Kalia police chief Sayeed Ahmed told bdnews24.com that acting on a tip-off, they raided a tea stall of Dighalia Bazar after dusk and arrested Maruf Hossain aka Anu. Also a former member of Bangladesh Ansars, Alam was an associate to another regional leader Dada Tapan who was killed in a 'crossfire' last year, Sayeed said. bdn
